debugToString() - Method in class calculator.BusinessLogic
This public toString method is used to display all the values of the BusinessLogic class in a textual representation for debugging purposes.
debugToString() - Method in class calculator.CalculatorValue
This is the debug toString method When more complex calculator values are creating this routine will need to be updated
displayBigNumber() - Method in class uNumberLibrary.UNumber
This routine is used to display big numbers on the console, 80 characters per line with the characteristic displayed on the last line (which might be longer than 80 characters in length).
displayShort() - Method in class uNumberLibrary.UNumber
This routine displays just the first 10 significant digits of a UNumber followed by the characteristic to System.out (the console).
div(CalculatorValue) - Method in class calculator.CalculatorValue
The following methods implement computation of division on the calculator values.
div(UNumber) - Method in class uNumberLibrary.UNumber
The divide operation implements division by means of repeated subtraction, producing as many significant digits in the quotient as in the dividend (this object) and the quotient replaces the dividend.
divE(CalculatorValue, CalculatorValue, CalculatorValue, CalculatorValue) - Method in class calculator.CalculatorValue
The following methods implement computation of division for the error terms.
division() - Method in class calculator.BusinessLogic
